     3. Identify Montana's Kids' Meals

     5. Recall Montana's desserts ","duration":1200,"type":"course","metatags":"General","rating":0,"selectionType":"course","category":"General","tags":[],"store":"library"}
155721|course237:
{"id":237,"name":"MO102B13E - Reading the Guest","description":"This module will demonstrate effective communication techniques for dealing with Guests and delivering Genuine Hospitality. Module content will cover listening skills, effective questioning techniques, handling concerns, uncovering Guests' needs and building rapport.

Learning Objectives:

By the end of the module, learners will be able to:
     1. Define the importance of developing rapport
     2. Recognize how body language is perceived by Guests
     3. Identify non-verbal communication signals
     4. Demonstrate how to handle concerns and complaints using the LAST technique
     5. Identify the benefits of using LAST technique
     6. Uncover effective questions to gauge Guests' needs
","duration":1800,"type":"course","metatags":"General","rating":0,"selectionType":"course","category":"General","tags":[],"store":"library"}
155721|course238:
{"id":238,"name":"MO102B14E - Enhancing the Guest Experience","description":"This module will review how to make recommendations and suggestions for Montana's food and drinks. Learners will learn how to utilize the techniques of up-selling and suggestive-selling through proper questioning skills, use of descriptive language, visual aids and the Product Knowledge Guide.

Learning Objectives:

By the end of this module, learners will be able to:
     1. Identify the difference between up-selling and suggestive-selling
     2. Identify techniques used in up-selling and suggestive selling
     3. Identify the difference between close questions and open questions
     4. Indicate the importance of using mouth-watering language to describe Montana's menu items
     5. Indicate how to use visual aids when making recommendations to Guests
","duration":2100,"type":"scorm","metatags":"General","rating":0,"selectionType":"course","category":"General","tags":[],"store":"library"}
155721|course239:
{"id":239,"name":"MO102B15E - Cookhouse Culture","description":"In this module, learners will learn about Montana's unique Children's and birthday programs. Learning Objectives:

By the end of the module, learners will be able to:
     1. Identify the benefits of Montana's unique programs
     2. Summarize Montana's 'Everyone and Always' principles
     3. Use Montana's unique terminology in sentences
     4. Select when to refill fountain drinks, coffee and tea
     5. Identify Montana's phone policy
","duration":1800,"type":"course","metatags":"General","rating":0,"selectionType":"course","category":"General","tags":[],"store":"library"}
155721|course240:
{"id":240,"name":"MO102B1E - Host Intro","description":"This module will provide learners with an understanding of the Host's role in delivering Montana's Genuine Hospitality. Learning Objectives:

By the end of the module, learners will be able to:
     1. Identify opportunities for the Host to interact with Guests
     2. Recall the key responsibilities of a Host
     3. Identify key opportunities to deliver Genuine Hospitality
     4. Differentiate between service statements and Genuine Hospitality statements ","duration":1200,"type":"course","metatags":"General","rating":0,"selectionType":"course","category":"General","tags":[],"store":"library"}
155721|course243:
{"id":243,"name":"MO102B2E - Server Intro","description":"Servers play a crucial role in delivering Genuine Hospitality. In this module, learners will understand the key responsibilities of a Server. Learning Objectives:

By the end of the module, learners will be able to:
     1. Identify key opportunities to deliver Genuine Hospitality
     2. Identify the key responsibilities within each opportunity
     3. Select tool belt items required for each shift
     4. Recognize Genuine Hospitality statements ","duration":1200,"type":"course","metatags":"General","rating":0,"selectionType":"course","category":"General","tags":[],"store":"library"}
155721|course245:
{"id":245,"name":"MO102B3E - Bartender Intro","description":"This module will provide learners with an understanding and appreciation of the role Bartenders play in delivering Genuine Hospitality. Rules and procedures pertaining to Guests alcohol consumption will be explained. Learning Objectives:

By the end of the module, learners will be able to:
     1. Indicate what is meant by 'corner bar theory'
     2. Indicate who is permitted behind the Montana's bar
     3. Indicate the ingredients in all Cookhouse Cocktails
     4. Recall the varieties of wine and beer offered at Montana's
     5. Recognize the signs of intoxication
     6. Recognize the procedure to be followed when 'cutting-off' a Guest
     7. Identify Montana's designated driver policy
     8. Identify how to proceed with a Guest who is displaying disorderly conduct
     9. Identify Service Bar protocol
     10. Recall the steps of wine service
     11. Recall the procedures for draft and bottle service
","duration":1800,"type":"course","metatags":"General","rating":0,"selectionType":"course","category":"General","tags":[],"store":"library"}
155721|course247:
{"id":247,"name":"MO102B4E - Expo Intro","description":"Though not in direct contact with Cookhouse Guests, the Expo has a powerful influence on the Guest experience. This 25 minute module will discuss the Expo's role in delivering Montana's Genuine Hospitality. Terminology will be defined and key responsibilities of the Expo will be described. Module content will include quality, consistency, and portion control as well as teamwork and running food.

Learning Objectives:
By the end of the module, learners will be able to:
     1. Identify the responsibilities of an Expo
     2. Recognize the importance of an Expo
     3. Recognize table and seating number's process
     4. Identify communication protocols with Service and Kitchen Associates
     5. Recognize portion control and accuracy for dishes
     6. Identify food chit process
     7. Identify re-cook chit process
     8. Match specific Expo terminology to definitions
","duration":1500,"type":"course","metatags":"General","rating":0,"selectionType":"course","category":"General","tags":[],"store":"library"}
155721|course248:
{"id":248,"name":"MO102B5E - Cookhouse Team","description":"In this module, learners will be introduced to the members of the Cookhouse team. By the end of this module, learners will be able to:
     1. Identify the key responsibilities of Service Associates

     5. Identify specific examples of how the Cookhouse team contributes to creating a perfect Guest Experience
","duration":1200,"type":"course","metatags":"General","rating":0,"selectionType":"course","category":"General","tags":[],"store":"library"}

{"id":251,"name":"MO102B7E - Host Essentials","description":"In this module, learners will be given a more in-depth understanding of the responsibilities of each Host role. By the end of the module, learners will be able to:
     1. Identify the duties attributed to each Host role
     2. Identify the Host's responsibilities during a wait
     3. Demonstrate how to use the floor plan to provide appropriate seating for Guests
     4. Recognize how to perform 'stage seating'
     5. Identify the Host's side duties
","duration":2400,"type":"course","metatags":"General","rating":0,"selectionType":"course","category":"General","tags":[],"store":"library"}
155721|course255:
{"id":255,"name":"MO102B9E - Bar Essentials","description":"Learners will gain in-depth knowledge of the various roles and responsibilities of a Montana's Bartender. They will be presented with skills and behaviors that are specific to the role of Bartending. Learners will review how to serve, pour and mix drinks and create the atmosphere outlined in the 'Corner Bar theory'. This module will provide instruction on the specific duties required by the Bartender to provide Montana's Genuine Hospitality at the bar.

Learning Objectives:

By the end of the module, learners will be able to:
     1. Indicate the proper alcoholic beverage specifications for Montana's signature drink menu
     2. Identify the proper glassware to accompany each Montana's drink
     3. Identify the steps of opening and closing the Bar

     5. Identify the role of the bar and the bartender during a Guest's wait
     6. Identify Montana's take out procedures ","duration":2400,"type":"course","metatags":"General","rating":0,"selectionType":"course","category":"General","tags":[],"store":"library"}
